<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7335> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7335" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Probably a senator in 129, named in the SC de agro Pergameno (Badian, Historia 12, 1963, 132; Sherk, RDGE 66, 70). If Cam. is the correct tribe for the Atilii Serrani (it seems to be Aem. in Joseph. AJ 14.239) this fragmentary name might be taken to be that of the consul of 106, C. Atilius Sex. f. Serranus (64) (Badian, loc. cit.). On the date, see M'. Aquillius (10), above.\n" ;
	dprr:hasID 7335 .
